by javiereguiluz at 2014-12-29T10:19:30Z

@karlosagudo thanks for your quick reply! There is still one very minor change to do related to this coding standard:

```
Add a blank line before return statements, unless the return is alone inside a
statement-group (like an if statement);
```

This means that there should be a blank line before the last `return` of the `getComposerVendorDir()` method.

And about the other errors displayed by fabbot and not related to this pull request, I think we can safely ignore them because they are related to PHPdoc contents alignment.

